{
  "id": "sys-12-google-chat-command-center",
  "name": "SYS 08 — Google Chat Command Center",
  "description": "Webhook at /google-chat-command. Parses natural-language commands via Claude (e.g. leads this week, pipeline status, overdue invoices, client health, revenue this month). Routes to the right handler, queries HubSpot or Sheets, formats a reply, and responds in Chat. Ad-hoc queries without opening n8n or HubSpot.",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## SYS 08 — Google Chat Command Center\n\n**Trigger:** Webhook POST at `/google-chat-command`.\n\n**Critical — Google Chat wiring:** Typing in a space does **not** call n8n by itself. **Incoming webhooks** (CONFIG `chatWebhookUrl`) only **send** messages **into** Chat; they cannot receive user text. You need a **Google Chat app** (Chat API → Configuration) with **HTTP endpoint URL** = your n8n webhook URL (`…/webhook/google-chat-command`). Users must **@mention the app** or **message it in DMs** (per Google). **Activate** this workflow in n8n. Endpoint must be **HTTPS** and reachable from Google.\n\n**What it does:** Parses commands via Claude; routes to HubSpot/Sheets; replies via HTTP to the space webhook from CONFIG.\n\n**Dependencies:** CONFIG, Call Claude API, HubSpot, Google Sheets (Revenue tab).\n\n**n8n 2.12.x:** Execute Sub-workflow = Database + `__rl`. **Prep Parse Prompt** reads Google **Event** shape (`message.text`, nested `event.message`, strips `<users/…>` mentions).",
        "height": 520,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "note-sys12",
      "name": "Note — About this workflow",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        80,
        80
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "google-chat-command",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
